notes: Just define the whole piece of 卯 and break down in our own way
The primitive for braces begins with the mouth full of staples
that you actually pay someone to inflict o n you. And as if this
weren't enough, the right side o f the primitive shows another
brace (a box facing left), reaching from your mouth all the way
around your head and back again, i n order t o keep your jaw
from growing while your teeth are growing straight.
Heisig breaks this down as water, mortar, bound up, cooking fire
In your example, heisig defines the entire four strokes in characters like 率 as a “sparkler"
Heisig views this 5 stroke version of 水 as snowflake
Heisig views all these “diagonal one strokes as variants of “droplet”
Heisig just calls the top three long parts hair in his story, and later defines this as a horse mane. For things like this we can do them independently, as long as they are cosnistent
